  "texts": [
    "This capability to simulate surgical operations in high fidelity enables surgeons to better understand complex patient-specific anatomy and make more informed decisions about surgical approaches, thus improving both strategy and patient outcomes [110,111].",
    "Furthermore, VR simulators enhanced with real-time object recognition and tracking can accurately identify instruments and anatomical structures, providing trainees with instant real-time feedback and bridging the gap between theory and practice [110].",
    "Generative AI-powered VR simulators can be used to assess metrics such as completion time, accuracy, tissue handling, and adherence to procedural steps, delivering data-driven feedback that helps pinpoint areas for improvement, facilitating focused practice [112].",
    "Additionally, post-operative feedback and motion analysis can further enhance the learning process [113].",
    "For instance, Vaughan et al."
